### =================================================================================
### PERSON 2 — END TO END TESTING SCRIPT
### Prequisite: Run `npx prisma db seed` to create Admin and Instructor accounts.
### Scenario: Instructor creates Quiz, Questions, Rewards. Then Instructor checks Reports.
### =================================================================================

# Global Variables
# SEEDED ACCOUNTS
@admin_email = admin@learnova.com
@admin_pass = Admin@1234
@instructor_email = instructor@learnova.com
@instructor_pass = Instructor@1234

# Use this course ID or replace with one from your DB
@course_id = cmn04iojp0002v6mfppnr3ljk
# Test student email for invitations
@student_email = 23bce200@nirmauni.ac.in



### 1. LOGIN AS ADMIN (To checking Admin access)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name adminLogin
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{admin_email}}",
  "password": "{{admin_pass}}"
}


### 2. LOGIN AS INSTRUCTOR (The one created by seed.js)
# (We need the token to do everything else)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name instructorLogin
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{instructor_email}}",
  "password": "{{instructor_pass}}"
}

### Store Token
@token = {{instructorLogin.response.body.token}}


### 3. QUIZ MANAGEMENT
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Create a Quiz for the Course
# @name createQuiz
POST http://localhost:5000/api/courses/{{course_id}}/quizzes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Final Exam - Module 1",
  "description": "This is the final assessment for the Backend module."
}

### Store Quiz ID
@quiz_id = {{createQuiz.response.body.id}}


### List Quizzes (Verify Creation)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/courses/{{course_id}}/quizzes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Update Quiz Title
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Final Exam - Module 1 (Revised)"
}


### 3. QUESTION MANAGEMENT
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Add Question 1
# @name addQuestion1
POST http://localhost:5000/api/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Which HTTP method is used to create a resource?",
  "order": 1
}

### 
@q1_id = {{addQuestion1.response.body.id}}


### Add Options for Question 1
POST http://localhost:5000/api/questions/{{q1_id}}/options
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "GET",
  "isCorrect": false,
  "order": 1
}

###
POST http://localhost:5000/api/questions/{{q1_id}}/options
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "POST",
  "isCorrect": true,
  "order": 2
}


### Add Question 2
# @name addQuestion2
POST http://localhost:5000/api/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Node.js is single-threaded.",
  "order": 2
}

### 
@q2_id = {{addQuestion2.response.body.id}}

### Add Options for Question 2
POST http://localhost:5000/api/questions/{{q2_id}}/options
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "True",
  "isCorrect": true,
  "order": 1
}

###
POST http://localhost:5000/api/questions/{{q2_id}}/options
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "False",
  "isCorrect": false,
  "order": 2
}


### 4. REWARDS MANAGEMENT
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Set Rewards for Quiz
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}/rewards
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rewards": [
    { "attemptNumber": 1, "points": 100 },
    { "attemptNumber": 2, "points": 75 },
    { "attemptNumber": 3, "points": 50 }
  ]
}


### 5. INVITATIONS
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Invite Student
POST http://localhost:5000/api/courses/{{course_id}}/invitations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{student_email}}"
}

### List Invitations
GET http://localhost:5000/api/courses/{{course_id}}/invitations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 6. REPORTING (Instructor View)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Get Overview Stats
GET http://localhost:5000/api/reporting
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Detailed Learner Progress
GET http://localhost:5000/api/reporting/users?courseId={{course_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### =================================================================================
### STUDENT SIDE (To complete the cycle - Optional for Person 2 but good for testing)
### =================================================================================

### Register Student (if not exists)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Nirma",
  "lastName": "Student",
  "email": "{{student_email}}",
  "password": "{{student_pass}}"
}

### Login as Student
# @name studentLogin
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{student_email}}",
  "password": "{{student_pass}}"
}

### 
@student_token = {{studentLogin.response.body.token}}

### Accept Invitation (Simulated - normally via email link)
# You need the token from the "List Invitations" response above.
# Replace TOKEN_HERE manually if testing flow.
# POST http://localhost:5000/api/invitations/accept/TOKEN_HERE